-- Aneka, Bumi Resources, Tower Bersama: Indonesian Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-02-09T01:25:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/aneka-bumi-resources-tower-bersama-indonesian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 0.8 percent to 3,988.70.  Nickel producers: Nickel futures fell for the first time in
four days, losing 1.4 percent to $21,500 a metric ton in London
yesterday.  PT Vale Indonesia (INCO)  , the nation’s largest
producer of the metal, dropped 1.3 percent to 3,850 rupiah and
 PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM)   rose 0.5 percent to 1,930 rupiah.  PT Bumi Resources (BUMI)  : Indonesia’s largest coal
producer obtained a four-year, $600 million loan from China
Development Bank Corp. to refinance debt, Investor Daily
Indonesia reported, citing Director Dileep Srivastava. Bumi was
unchanged at 2,475 rupiah.  PT Tower Bersama Infrastructure (TBIG)  : The company
signed a $406 million agreement to purchase 2,500 cellular
towers from  PT Indosat (ISAT)  , Tower Bersama said yesterday.
Tower Bersama advanced 3 percent to 2,575 rupiah and Indosat,
Indonesia’s second-biggest mobile phone operator, slipped 0.9
percent to 5,350 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
